b) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
c) Ensure the brake is engaged to avoid early release of the anchor; 
d) Ensure all sea-going securing devices are removed; 
e) Walk out the anchor, using the winch, until it is clear of any obstructions and to ensure the anchor is free; 
f) Under no circumstances should the crew kick or manually move a seized anchor chain whilst the break is disengaged; 
g) Any crew not directly involved in anchor operations should stay well clear.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="2"><my:Description>Debris</my:Description><my:Severity>1</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>2</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, goggles, dust mask; 
