b) VHF radio check prior to operations; 
c) Use of the English language in clear and concise orders; 
d) Use of headphones in conjunction with the VHF.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="5"><my:Description>Slips and trips</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Trip hazards to be clearly marked; 
